stylometry: RiskSimtable allows you to figure out the best quantity of inventory to purchase at a given time in an EOQ model based on several estimated quantities.  In a normal distribution model you would find your standard deviation based on the demand and average (mean).  For the problem we did in class we wanted to find out how many calendars to purchase for inventory so we came up with 5 different order quantities.  We run those order quantities through RiskSimtable so say they were in excel as: B5;B6;B7;B8;B9 then we would go to the cell labled as order quantity and put in the formula =RISKSIMTABLE(B5:B19) and then run @Risk with 5 solutions since there are 5 quantities and with 1000 iterations and it would determine the best possible quantity to order based on standard deviation and demand.
